reviews.review:
Initially I was hesitant to play this game; to me, it felt like a preliminary cash grab to the upcoming hype of the Friday the 13th game. I thought the perks system was a bit of an overtune to key the survivors to get stronger and better in order to win and I have to say I was completely wrong;

After the introduction of the now-latest DLC Freddy; one of my favorite horror villains, I decided to give it a try. The game hones a certain atmosphere that keeps you on your toes, whether you are striving to survive or stalking your prey as the killer, it forces you to stay one step ahead. The perks have a fair enough chance for both sides to come out on top. The music, the location, the very feeling of tension that comes from the suspense of a genuine horror movie has a heavy hand in every match. Sure it has its share of issues; killers who camp hooked survivors, survivors who try to body block and blind the killer, which when coordinated, has foiled me countless times. But there's a degree of setbacks in every game.

All-in-all it is an amazing game, especially when playing with friends whether it's surviving with them or killing them all one-by-one it's hard not to say "One more match" and actually mean it. I've never been so wrong with my initial impressions of a game before.
